description:
## Problem

Mayor boot fails when checking hook status. Error blocks autonomous operation (GUPP violation).

## Error
```
Error: Database out of sync with JSONL. Run 'bd sync --import-only' to fix.
```

## Root Cause

File: /Users/looneym/gt/gastown/mayor/rig/internal/cmd/hook.go:146-152

gt hook uses beads.List() directly, bypassing bd CLI auto-import. When JSONL is newer than database (e.g., after git pull), sees stale data and fails.

## Solution: Self-Healing Retry

Add auto-import on sync error with retry:

```go
// Around line 145-152 in hook.go
existingPinned, err := b.List(beads.ListOptions{
    Status:   beads.StatusHooked,
    Assignee: agentID,
    Priority: -1,
})
if err != nil {
    // Try auto-import on first failure
    if strings.Contains(err.Error(), "out of sync") {
        importCmd := exec.Command("bd", "import", "-i", filepath.Join(workDir, "issues.jsonl"))
        _ = importCmd.Run()
        // Retry after import
        existingPinned, err = b.List(beads.ListOptions{
            Status:   beads.StatusHooked,
            Assignee: agentID,
            Priority: -1,
        })
    }
    if err != nil {
        return fmt.Errorf("checking existing hooked beads: %w", err)
    }
}
```

## Testing

1. Modify .beads/issues.jsonl externally
2. Run gt hook (should auto-import and succeed)
3. Test with Mayor boot after git pull
4. Verify no manual intervention needed

## Success Criteria

- gt hook works after external JSONL changes
- No manual bd import required
- Mayor boot propulsion maintained
- GUPP compliance restored
